My idea is to try to tackle the rewrite of importchecker.py at some point to use the ast module so it can be more reliable.

The main idea behind this is that plone, on the way to become a python 3 citizen it should also clean up its completely tangled dependency graph. If we don't get all the dependencies on setup.py first, that's nearly to impossible, so we need z3c.dependencychecker to help us on that!

This has been requested by several users. For time independent calculations (i.e. all calculations so far) the year can be assigned randomly. For instance if `investigation_time=50` and there are 3 stochastic event sets, the year will be:

- a random number between 1 and 50 for the first SES;
- a random number between 51 and 100 for the second SES;
- a  random number between 101 and 150 for the third SES.

Extra care is taken so that calculations are reproducible: the seed is fixed and the events are sorted by rupture serial number. The demos are running here: https://ci.openquake.org/job/zdevel_oq-engine/2295

