We increasingly implement configuration via environment variables, but we our
pubsub media type conventions tend to use naming schemas that can't be expressed
using environment variables. In particular, using previous logic, we'd want to
generate a configuration dictionar with something like:

    {
      "sns_topic_arns": {
        "mappings": {
          "application/vnd.globality.pubsub._.created.foo_bar.baz": "topic-name",
        }
      }
    }

While the microcosm environment variable loader can handle nested dictionaries
(via double underscores), we cannot express '/' or '.' because they aren't legal
characters.

We solve this problem in two ways:

 1. We add support for the convention-driven media types using alternative keys (avoiding '/')
 2. We (re)collapse double underscores within these convention keys (avoiding '.')

That is, we implement the above mapping using:

    {
      "sns_topic_arns": {
        "created": {
          "foo_bar": {
            "baz": "topic-name",
          },
        }
      }
    }

